SIMPLE: four-in-hand
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: four-in-hand
<hw>four-in-hand</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A long necktie that
is tied in a slipknot with one end hanging in front of the
other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a coach pulled by four horses with one
driver.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coach, coach-and-four.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fourierism</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Four-in-hand
<hw>Four"-in-hand</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Consisting of
four horses controlled by one person; <as>as, a <ex>four-in-hand</ex>
team</as>; drawn by four horses driven by one person; <as>as, a
<ex>four-in-hand</ex> coach</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
team of four horses driven by one person; also, a vehicle drawn by such
a team.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As quaint a <qex>four-in-hand</qex>⟦br⟧
As you shall see.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>four-lane</ent>⟦br⟧
